@startmindmap
* Ouroboros PoS
** The problem
*** Agree on one chain, no coordinator
*** Byzantine fault tolerance
*** Who / what / when
** PoW vs PoS
*** PoW: cost is electricity
*** PoS: cost is staked capital
*** Attack cost = 51% of stake
** Time structure
*** Slot = 1 second
*** Epoch = 432,000 slots (5 days)
*** ~1 block / 20 seconds
** Slot leader election
*** VRF evaluated locally per slot
*** Private until block published
*** Proportional to stake
*** Verifiable via VRF proof
*** Zero or many leaders per slot
** Stake snapshot
*** Taken 2 epochs earlier
*** Blocks rapid-stake attacks
** Chain selection
*** Longest chain rule
*** Praos tie-break by leader VRF
*** k = 2160 settlement bound
** Block-production keys
*** VRF key (election)
*** KES key (forward-secure signing)
*** Cold keys (offline root)
** Incentives
*** Rewards from fees + expansion
*** k0 = 500 target pools
*** Saturation caps oversized pools
*** Pledge resists Sybil
** Finality
*** Probabilistic
*** ~5-10 min practical
@endmindmap
